-- 18. Folkestone × Digital Marketing
INSERT INTO public.local_content (service_slug, town_slug, intro_paragraph, local_context, competition_landscape, success_approach, local_stats, pain_points, solutions, faqs, layout_variant)
VALUES (
  'digital-marketing',
  'folkestone',
  'Digital marketing in Folkestone requires a strategy that accounts for the town''s unique position as a regenerating coastal creative hub with growing tourism, an influx of new residents, and proximity to Continental Europe. The audiences are diverse: tourists planning a Harbour Arm visit, new residents seeking local services, established residents who value loyalty, and the Channel-adjacent business community. A single marketing campaign cannot reach all of them effectively. Our digital marketing strategies for Folkestone businesses are multi-channel, segment-specific, and tied directly to measurable outcomes, ensuring every pound spent connects your business with the right Folkestone customer at the right moment in their journey.',
  'Folkestone''s digital audience is growing rapidly. The town''s regeneration story generates national press coverage that drives search traffic. Social media engagement around the Harbour Arm and Creative Quarter creates awareness that extends well beyond Kent. New residents moving to Folkestone bring digital-first habits and actively search for local services online. The Saga workforce represents a concentrated, affluent professional demographic. Seasonal tourism creates predictable demand peaks that reward well-timed marketing campaigns.',
  'Digital marketing sophistication in Folkestone is developing but still below the Kent average. A few Harbour Arm restaurants invest in targeted social advertising. Some Creative Quarter businesses run occasional Google Ads. Most Folkestone businesses rely on organic social media and word of mouth, with no paid digital marketing strategy. The competitive landscape is wide open for businesses willing to invest strategically.',
  'We build Folkestone digital marketing strategies around the town''s natural audience segments. Tourist-focused campaigns run ahead of peak seasons and major events. Resident-focused campaigns target service keywords year-round. New-resident campaigns capture people searching for local services after moving. Each segment receives targeted messaging through the most appropriate channel, with conversion tracking showing exactly which campaigns generate customers.',
  '{"population": 51337, "business_count": "1800+", "key_areas": ["Creative Quarter", "Harbour Arm", "The Leas", "Cheriton", "Sandgate", "Channel Tunnel corridor"]}',
  '[{"title": "No paid marketing strategy in a growing Folkestone market", "description": "While Folkestone''s economy grows through regeneration and tourism, most local businesses rely entirely on word of mouth and organic social media. They miss the opportunity to capture new residents searching for services, tourists planning visits, and the growing digital audience that the town''s renaissance has created."}, {"title": "Marketing messages that do not differentiate Folkestone audiences", "description": "A tourist visiting the Harbour Arm has completely different needs from a Cheriton homeowner searching for a plumber. Folkestone businesses that run one generic campaign targeting everyone effectively reach nobody. Without audience segmentation, marketing budget is wasted on irrelevant impressions."}, {"title": "Seasonal revenue swings with no marketing strategy to smooth them", "description": "Folkestone businesses in tourism-adjacent sectors experience dramatic seasonal swings. Summer is overwhelming, winter is quiet. Without targeted digital marketing to drive off-peak demand and capture advance bookings during peak periods, revenue remains unpredictable and growth is impossible."}]',
  '[{"title": "Segment-specific Folkestone marketing campaigns", "description": "We create distinct campaigns for each Folkestone audience segment. Tourist campaigns drive advance bookings and awareness. Resident campaigns capture local service demand. New-resident campaigns welcome arrivals with introductory offers. Each segment is reached through the channels they actually use."}, {"title": "Seasonal marketing strategy for Folkestone businesses", "description": "We build marketing calendars around Folkestone''s seasonal patterns, ramping up tourism campaigns before summer and Harbour Arm season, targeting local services during quieter months, and creating event-specific campaigns around the Triennial and other cultural moments."}, {"title": "Attribution and ROI tracking for every Folkestone campaign", "description": "We implement conversion tracking across all channels so you see exactly which campaigns generate Folkestone enquiries. Monthly reports show cost per lead, customer acquisition cost, and return on investment by audience segment and channel, enabling data-driven budget decisions."}]',
  '[{"question": "What digital marketing budget should a Folkestone business start with?", "answer": "Folkestone''s lower competition compared to larger Kent towns means your budget goes further here. Many businesses see meaningful results starting from three hundred to five hundred pounds per month in ad spend. We provide a detailed market analysis and forecast so you can start with confidence."}, {"question": "Can digital marketing help me fill quiet periods in Folkestone?", "answer": "Absolutely. Targeted campaigns during off-peak months can drive significant demand. For hospitality, we promote winter experiences, midweek offers, and event-related bookings. For services, we target the consistent year-round demand that exists beneath the seasonal tourism peaks."}, {"question": "Should I advertise to tourists visiting Folkestone?", "answer": "If your business serves visitors, yes. Tourist-focused Google and Instagram campaigns targeting people searching for Folkestone experiences, restaurants, and accommodation are highly effective. We time these campaigns to match booking windows, typically four to six weeks ahead of peak periods."}, {"question": "How do I know if my Folkestone digital marketing is working?", "answer": "We set up conversion tracking from day one so every enquiry, booking, or sale is attributed to a specific campaign. Monthly reporting shows your cost per customer, return on ad spend, and which Folkestone audience segments deliver the best results. No vanity metrics, only commercial outcomes."}]',
  'lead-gen'
)
